tachyon.exception

Class TachyonException

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Exception
        • tachyon.exception.TachyonException
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AccessControlException, BlockAlreadyExistsException, BlockDoesNotExistException, BlockInfoException, ConnectionFailedException, DependencyDoesNotExistException, DirectoryNotEmptyException, FailedToCheckpointException, FileAlreadyCompletedException, FileAlreadyExistsException, FileDoesNotExistException, InvalidFileSizeException, InvalidPathException, InvalidWorkerStateException, LineageDeletionException, LineageDoesNotExistException, NoWorkerException, WorkerOutOfSpaceException

    public abstract class TachyonException
extends Exception
    General TachyonException used throughout the system. It must be able serialize itself to the RPC framework and convert back without losing any necessary information.
